onstruct a meaningful world within the disenchantment of modernity. Sumathi Ramaswamy ultimately reveals how loss itself has become a condition of modernity, compelling us to rethink the politics of imagination and creativity in our day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCivilization, Ancient. 0aCivilization, Classical. 0aLost continents. 0aTamil (Indic people)zIndiaxHistory. 0aTamil (Indic people). 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aafrica.  aanthropology.  aantiquity.  aarchaeology.  aart history.  aatlantis.  aaustralia.  acharles darwin.  acivilization.  acolonial.  acolonialism.  adarwinism.  aethnography.  aevolution.  ageographic.  ageography.  ageology.  agrief.  ahimalayas.  aindian ocean.  alemuria.  aloss.  amaps.  aoccult.  aoccultism.  apacific ocean.  aracism.  aregional.  atamil.  atibet.  autopian.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024032240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093185540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931855423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931855/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY